Description:
THE VIRGINIA CENTER FOR POLICING INNOVATION (VCPI), IN PARTNERSHIP WITH CNA, THE DEVELOPER OF MANAGING BIAS (MB) TRAINING CURRICULUM FOR LAW ENFORCEMENT AGENCIES, WILL DELIVER AND EXPAND NATIONALLY THE EXPANSION OF THE MB TRAINING PROGRAM ENCOURAGING LAW ENFORCEMENT TO UNDERSTAND TOLERANCE.  PROGRAM DELIVERABLES INCLUDE DIRECTLY TRAINING 1,500 TRAINERS TO INSTRUCT THE MB COURSE IN THEIR OWN JURISDICTIONS, SUPPORTING UP TO 75,000 LAW ENFORCEMENT PRACTITIONERS TRAINED NATIONWIDE; A CERTIFIED NATIONAL CORE CADRE OF MANAGING BIAS FOR LAW ENFORCEMENT IDP INSTRUCTORS; A MANAGING BIAS ONLINE RESOURCE CENTER AND CORRESPONDING, MICRO-LEARNING ONLINE TRAINING INITIATIVE (DELIVERED VIA THE COPS PORTAL TO A MINIMUM OF 3,500 OFFICERS).  SPECIFIC PROGRAM DELIVERABLES THAT WILL COME OUT OF THIS AWARD INCLUDE: 


	A MULTI-FACETED NATIONAL INSTRUCTOR DEVELOPMENT PROGRAM (IDP), DELIVERED IN 50 ONSITE MANAGING BIAS IDP COURSES (ONE IN EACH STATE), DIRECTLY TRAINING 1,500 TO INSTRUCT THE COURSE IN THEIR OWN JURISDICTIONS, SUPPORTING UP TO 75,000 LAW ENFORCEMENT PRACTITIONERS TRAINED NATIONWIDE; 
	A CERTIFIED NATIONAL CORE CADRE OF MANAGING BIAS FOR LAW ENFORCEMENT IDP INSTRUCTORS;
	A MANAGING BIAS ONLINE RESOURCE CENTER;
	A CORRESPONDING, MICRO-LEARNING ONLINE TRAINING INITIATIVE (DELIVERED VIA THE COPS PORTAL TO A MINIMUM OF 3,500 OFFICERS); AND
	A RIGOROUS EVALUATION TO DETERMINE PROGRAMMATIC IMPACT AND EFFICACY AND THE IMPACT OF CONTINUED APPLICATION OF MICRO LEARNING ON TRAINING.
